race.comment: SHAMWARI (3) was an impressive maiden winner last start, cruising home by 3 lengths here over a mile 17 days ago. He cops a tough gate, but is bred to keep on improving with time, and he can repeat the dose. KEEPING TIME (9) was close up when resuming, finishing runner-up by less than a length over 1300m at Woodville nearly 3 weeks ago after racing on the pace throughout. She strips fitter, and with Bruno Queiroz in the irons this time, she can go one better. LEAVE A LIGHT ON (10) did not run up to expectations last season despite having plenty of market support. She is not out of this. MAGIC CHARM (4) has not run on after getting too far back in both of his starts back from a spell. He can settle closer to the pace from a superior gate, and a form reversal is on the cards. OUTER FOCUS (5) closed strongly to be beaten into second by just a length last time out at Woodville nearly 3 weeks ago. Stick with him on an each-way basis.
